Half of the six-member city council in Ferguson will now be African-American . 
  The lone black incumbent councilman Dwayne James was not up for re-election . 
  The election came just over a month after the Justice Department released a report on the culture of racism and abuse in the city . 
  Wesley Bell defeated another black candidate to win in the 3rd Ward . 
  Ella Jones defeated two white candidates in the 1st Ward . 
  Brian Fletcher, a former mayor who is white, won in the 2nd Ward . 
 